# go_router Conventions

## Route Paths

Route paths must match the table in `docs/ProxDroid_Architecture.md §8`:

```
/                          → redirect → /servers or /dashboard
/servers                   → Server list
/servers/add               → Add server
/servers/edit/:serverId    → Edit server
/dashboard                 → Node overview
/dashboard/:node           → Node detail + charts
/vms                       → VM list
/vms/:node/:vmid           → VM detail + charts
/containers                → Container list
/containers/:node/:ctid    → Container detail
/storage                   → Storage overview
/storage/:node/:storage    → Storage detail
/backups                   → Backup list
/tasks                     → Task viewer
/tasks/:node/:upid         → Task detail + log
/settings                  → Settings
```

Do not invent new top-level routes. Add sub-routes only when they match a
feature screen in the roadmap.

## Typed Path Parameters

Use these exact parameter names — other names will break downstream code that
extracts them by name:

- `:node` — Proxmox node name
- `:vmid` — VM ID (integer, but passed as string in the path)
- `:ctid` — Container ID
- `:upid` — Task UPID (must be percent-encoded — see below)
- `:serverId` — Local server UUID
- `:storage` — Storage pool name

## Redirect: Null selectedServerProvider

The go_router `redirect` callback must redirect API-requiring routes to
`/servers` when `selectedServerProvider` is null (no server configured):

API-requiring routes (redirect to `/servers` when server is null):
`/dashboard`, `/vms`, `/containers`, `/storage`, `/backups`, `/tasks`

Always-accessible routes (must work without a configured server):
`/servers`, `/servers/add`, `/servers/edit/:serverId`, `/settings`

Without this redirect, API providers fire without a server and crash.

## UPID Percent-Encoding

Proxmox UPIDs contain colons (e.g. `UPID:node:0000ABCD:00000001:5F3E45A2:qmstart:100:root@pam:`).
Raw colons in a URL path segment are interpreted as path separators by go_router
and will cause navigation to fail.

When pushing `/tasks/:node/:upid`, always percent-encode the UPID:

```dart
// Pushing the route — encode the UPID
context.push('/tasks/$node/${Uri.encodeComponent(upid)}');
```

When receiving the UPID in the destination screen, decode it:

```dart
// In TaskDetailScreen — decode the param
final upid = Uri.decodeComponent(state.pathParameters['upid']!);
```

Never push a raw UPID into the URL path without encoding.
